                                <comments>
                            <comment id="17533711" author="krummas" created="Mon, 9 May 2022 09:07:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/pull/1611&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/pull/1611&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;increases timeout from 10s to 1 minute for the repair messages&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;additionally bumps timeout for VALIDATION_RSP to 5 minutes&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;adds an error callback when sending SYNC_REQ and VALIDATION_REQ messages to avoid the hanging repairs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;tests: &lt;a href=&quot;https://app.circleci.com/pipelines/github/krummas/cassandra?branch=marcuse%2F17613&amp;amp;filter=all&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://app.circleci.com/pipelines/github/krummas/cassandra?branch=marcuse%2F17613&amp;amp;filter=all&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17575941" author="edimitrova" created="Fri, 5 Aug 2022 16:23:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=marcuse&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;marcuse&quot;&gt;marcuse&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=dcapwell&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;dcapwell&quot;&gt;dcapwell&lt;/a&gt;&#160;if this is a long known issue and not recent regression, is this ticket a beta blocker?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17576874" author="dcapwell" created="Mon, 8 Aug 2022 16:10:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;the 4.0 branch I am +1 with minor comments, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=marcuse&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;marcuse&quot;&gt;marcuse&lt;/a&gt; should we block 4.1?  Think we would need to as the 4.0 branch would assume that 4.1.0 would support this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
